{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"cardiac-lush-chihuahua","description":"# 1.0 release hygiene: dependabot, classifier bump, stability-promise flip, RC decision (tag signing: explicit skip)\n\n## Why\n\nThese are the final mechanical artifacts for the 1.0 declaration, sized to what 2026 peers actually do — which notably REVERSES two earlier assumptions. (1) Signed git tags are no longer convergent: of CPython/pip/ruff/uv/pytest/httpx, zero sign new release tags in 2026 (CPython dropped GPG at 3.14 per PEP 761; ruff/uv/httpx use lightweight tags); the baseline is annotated tags + GitHub immutable releases + PEP 740 attestations — all of which rebar already has. (2) RC trains are not convergent: pydantic v2 shipped beta→final in 13 days with zero rcs; attrs/structlog skipped 1.0 entirely; the load-bearing artifact is the written compatibility policy, which `docs/api-stability.md` already is.\n\n## What\n\n- `.github/dependabot.yml`, the pip/pydantic minimal pattern: `github-actions` ecosystem ONLY, monthly, one catch-all group, cooldown 7 days. No `pip` entry — version updates act on pins/lockfiles, and rebar's unpinned `>=` core deps give them nothing to do but make noise; security ALERTS fire regardless of this file. Record that rationale as comments inside the file. Add a `uv` block only if a `uv.lock` is ever committed.\n- Staged for the v1.0.0 release change itself: bump `Development Status :: 4 - Beta` → `5 - Production/Stable` (pyproject.toml classifier), and flip the pre-1.0 caveat in `docs/api-stability.md` so the stability matrix becomes the operative SemVer promise (the doc already anticipates exactly this flip).\n- `docs/releasing.md`: record the DECISION to skip tag signing, with rationale (2026 peer baseline; attestations cover artifact provenance) and a revisit trigger (workflow-compromise entering the threat model, or a downstream consumer asking to verify tags); confirm annotated (not lightweight) tags remain the practice and immutable releases stay on.\n- RC decision — record and execute one of: (a) a single `1.0.0rc1` (PEP 440 spelling — not `-rc.1`; pre-releases are invisible to plain `pip install`, so publishing one is inherently safe) with a 1–2 week window announced as a GitHub pre-release; or (b) skip the RC entirely. Default: skip unless an external adopter materializes to actually test it — an RC only buys data if someone runs it, and `1.0.1` is the de-facto rc for a small tool. Both options are convergence-compatible; record the choice + rationale.\n- Record explicit deferrals as non-goals: SBOM/license-scan tooling beyond GitHub's dependency-graph export; Renovate; a lockfile for the optional extras (revisit post-1.0).\n\n## Scope\n\nIN: `.github/dependabot.yml`, the pyproject classifier + api-stability flip (staged, may land in the 1.0 release change — reference it), `docs/releasing.md` decision records, the RC decision.\nOUT: executing the release itself (existing runbook); the contract-freeze code work (exit codes / error envelope / MCP schema pin — tracked elsewhere); SBOM tooling; CI matrix changes (Windows explicitly out — classifiers claim POSIX/macOS, consistent today).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `dependabot.yml` committed: github-actions-only, monthly, grouped, cooldown 7, rationale comment inside.\n- [ ] Classifier bump + api-stability caveat flip staged and referenced from this ticket (landing vehicle identified).\n- [ ] Tag-signing skip decision + revisit trigger recorded in `docs/releasing.md`.\n- [ ] RC decision recorded with rationale; if rc chosen, PEP 440 spelling (`1.0.0rc1`) verified against the release workflow's tag pattern.\n- [ ] Deferral list (SBOM, Renovate, extras lockfile) recorded on the ticket.","id":"fc9e-677e-a271-4678","parent_id":"fc2a-9fa5-def6-4e68","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"1.0 release hygiene: dependabot, classifier bump, stability-promise flip, RC decision"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783628679634743001,"uuid":"00f7f448-5f32-420b-84ee-e0ccf78ab4f4"}